== Births == * [[Ōei]] 11th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1404]] {{ill|July 6|ja|7月6日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Yamana Sōzen|ja|山名宗全|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (also known as Mochiyutaka), a military commander (died [[1473]])<ref>{{Harvnb|百目木|1918|p=2}}</ref>. * [[Eishō]] 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1517]] {{ill|June 18|ja|6月18日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Shin-chikamachi Tennō|ja|正親町天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 106th Emperor of Japan (died [[1593]]). * [[Genna]] 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1618]] {{ill|July 21|ja|7月21日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hayashi Ga-hō|ja|林鵞峰|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (also known as Shunsai), a Confucian scholar and the son of Hayashi Razan (died [[1680]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1819]] {{ill|July 20|ja|7月20日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Tokugawa Saion|ja|徳川斉温|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 11th daimyō of the Owari Domain (died [[1839]]). * Bunkyū 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1862, June 26) – {{ill|Minasaku Motohachi|ja|箕作元八|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a historian and the fourth son of Minasaku Akutsubo (died [[1919]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Kenkyū|ja|建久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1193]] {{ill|June 29|ja|6月29日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Soga Jigorō Tokuchi|ja|曾我五郎時致|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a samurai and the younger brother of Soga (born [[1174]]). * [[Tenmei]] 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1788]] {{ill|July 2|ja|7月2日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Goryōken Kayū|ja|呉陵軒可有|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a miscellaneous haiku writer known as "Yanudaru" (柳多留). * [[Bunka]] 14th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1817]] {{ill|July 13|ja|7月13日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Kaiho Seiryō|ja|海保青陵|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Confucian scholar and economic reformer (born [[1755]]).
