{{Lunisolar May}} '''May 29''' is the 29th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft}}. If the month is {{Nihongo|Small|小}} then this is the last day of the month. Otherwise, if the month is {{Nihongo|Big|大}}, then it is the second last day.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref> Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1862]] {{ill|June 26|ja|6月26日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – In the 【Second Tōzenji Incident|{{ill|Tōzenji Incident|ja|東禅寺事件|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}】, a samurai from the Matsumoto domain who was assigned to guard the provisional British legation at Tōzenji in Edo invaded and killed two British seamen.<ref>{{Cite book |和書 |author=池田正一郎 |title=日本災変通志 |publisher=新人物往来社 |year=2004-12-15 |page=721 |isbn=4-404-03190-4}}</ref> * [[Meiji 4]] ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1872]] {{ill|July 16|ja|7月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – A large fire broke out in Yoshiwara, with two-thirds of the red-light district burning down; 678 households were destroyed. * Meiji 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1872]] {{ill|July 4|ja|7月4日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Tokyo Normal School (later Tokyo Education University, now part of Tsukuba University) was established.
== Births == * [[Ōei]] 11th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1404]] {{ill|July 6|ja|7月6日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Yamana Sōzen|ja|山名宗全|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (also known as Mochiyutaka), a military commander (died [[1473]])<ref>{{Harvnb|百目木|1918|p=2}}</ref>. * [[Eishō]] 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1517]] {{ill|June 18|ja|6月18日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Shin-chikamachi Tennō|ja|正親町天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 106th Emperor of Japan (died [[1593]]). * [[Genna]] 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1618]] {{ill|July 21|ja|7月21日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hayashi Ga-hō|ja|林鵞峰|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (also known as Shunsai), a Confucian scholar and the son of Hayashi Razan (died [[1680]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1819]] {{ill|July 20|ja|7月20日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Tokugawa Saion|ja|徳川斉温|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 11th daimyō of the Owari Domain (died [[1839]]). * Bunkyū 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1862, June 26) – {{ill|Minasaku Motohachi|ja|箕作元八|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a historian and the fourth son of Minasaku Akutsubo (died [[1919]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Kenkyū|ja|建久|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1193]] {{ill|June 29|ja|6月29日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Soga Jigorō Tokuchi|ja|曾我五郎時致|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a samurai and the younger brother of Soga (born [[1174]]). * [[Tenmei]] 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1788]] {{ill|July 2|ja|7月2日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Goryōken Kayū|ja|呉陵軒可有|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a miscellaneous haiku writer known as "Yanudaru" (柳多留). * [[Bunka]] 14th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1817]] {{ill|July 13|ja|7月13日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Kaiho Seiryō|ja|海保青陵|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Confucian scholar and economic reformer (born [[1755]]).
