{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月廿九|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 29일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May|qq=}} '''May 29''' is the 29th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|qq=draft}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft}}. If the month is {{Nihongo|Small|小|qq=}} then this is the last day of the month. Otherwise, if the month is {{Nihongo|Big|大|qq=}}, then it is the second last day.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref> Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=|qq=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|qq=|qq=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1862]] {{ill|June 26|ja|6月26日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – In the 【Second Tōzenji Incident|{{ill|Tōzenji Incident|ja|東禅寺事件|qq=|qq=draft}}】, a samurai from the Matsumoto domain who was assigned to guard the provisional British legation at Tōzenji in Edo invaded and killed two British seamen.<ref>{{Cite book |和書 |author=池田正一郎 |title=日本災変通志 |publisher=新人物往来社 |year=2004-12-15 |page=721 |isbn=4-404-03190-4|qq=}}</ref> * [[Meiji 4]] ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1872]] {{ill|July 16|ja|7月16日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – A large fire broke out in Yoshiwara, with two-thirds of the red-light district burning down; 678 households were destroyed. * Meiji 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1872]] {{ill|July 4|ja|7月4日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – Tokyo Normal School (later Tokyo Education University, now part of Tsukuba University) was established.
