{{Not to be confused with|May 29|qq=May 29}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月廿九|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 29일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May|qq=}} '''May 29''' is the 29th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. If the month is {{Nihongo|Small|小|qq=}} then this is the last day of the month. Otherwise, if the month is {{Nihongo|Big|大|qq=}}, then it is the second last day.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref> Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senbu|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1862]] [[:en:June 26|June 26]]) – In the 【Second Tōzenji Incident|{{ill|Tōzenji Incident|ja|東禅寺事件|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōzenji Incident|qq=}}】, a samurai from the Matsumoto domain who was assigned to guard the provisional British legation at Tōzenji in Edo invaded and killed two British seamen.<ref>{{Cite book |和書 |author=池田正一郎 |title=日本災変通志 |publisher=新人物往来社 |year=2004-12-15 |page=721 |isbn=4-404-03190-4|qq=}}</ref> * [[Meiji 4]] ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1872]] [[:en:July 16|July 16]]) – A large fire broke out in Yoshiwara, with two-thirds of the red-light district burning down; 678 households were destroyed. * Meiji 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1872]] [[:en:July 4|July 4]]) – Tokyo Normal School (later Tokyo Education University, now part of Tsukuba University) was established.
== Births == * [[Ōei]] 11th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1404]] [[:en:July 6|July 6]]) – [[:en:Yamana Sōzen|Yamana Sōzen]] (also known as Mochiyutaka), a military commander (died [[1473]])<ref>{{Harvnb|百目木|1918|p=2|qq=}}</ref>. * [[Eishō]] 14th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1517]] [[:en:June 18|June 18]]) – [[:en:Emperor Ōgimachi|Shin-chikamachi Tennō]], the 106th Emperor of Japan (died [[1593]]). * [[Genna]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1618]] [[:en:July 21|July 21]]) – [[:en:Hayashi Gahō|Hayashi Ga-hō]] (also known as Shunsai), a Confucian scholar and the son of Hayashi Razan (died [[1680]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1819]] [[:en:July 20|July 20]]) – [[:en:Tokugawa Nariharu|Tokugawa Saion]], the 11th daimyō of the Owari Domain (died [[1839]]). * Bunkyū 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] 1862, June 26) – {{ill|Minasaku Motohachi|ja|箕作元八|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minasaku Motohachi|qq=}}, a historian and the fourth son of Minasaku Akutsubo (died [[1919]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Kenkyū|Kenkyū]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1193]] [[:en:June 29|June 29]]) – {{ill|Soga Jigorō Tokuchi|ja|曾我五郎時致|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Soga Jigorō Tokuchi|qq=}}, a samurai and the younger brother of Soga (born [[1174]]). * [[Tenmei]] 8th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1788]] [[:en:July 2|July 2]]) – {{ill|Goryōken Kayū|ja|呉陵軒可有|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Goryōken Kayū|qq=}}, a miscellaneous haiku writer known as "Yanudaru" (柳多留). * [[Bunka]] 14th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1817]] [[:en:July 13|July 13]]) – {{ill|Kaiho Seiryō|ja|海保青陵|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaiho Seiryō|qq=}}, a Confucian scholar and economic reformer (born [[1755]]).
== Commemorations == == See Also == {{Lunar Calendar See Also|5|28|5|30|4|29|6|5|0529|qq=}}
