== Births == * [[:en:Ōei|Ōei]] 11th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1404|1404]] [[:en:July 6|July 6]]) – [[:en:Yamana Sōzen|Yamana Sōzen]] (also known as Mochiyutaka), a military commander (died [[:en:1473|1473]])<ref>{{Harvnb|百目木|1918|p=2|qq=}}</ref>. * [[:en:Eishō|Eishō]] 14th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1517|1517]] [[:en:June 18|June 18]]) – [[:en:Emperor Ōgimachi|Shin-chikamachi Tennō]], the 106th Emperor of Japan (died [[:en:1593|1593]]). * [[Genna]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1618|1618]] [[:en:July 21|July 21]]) – [[:en:Hayashi Gahō|Hayashi Ga-hō]] (also known as Shunsai), a Confucian scholar and the son of Hayashi Razan (died [[:en:1680|1680]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1819|1819]] [[:en:July 20|July 20]]) – [[:en:Tokugawa Nariharu|Tokugawa Saion]], the 11th daimyō of the Owari Domain (died [[:en:1839|1839]]). * Bunkyū 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] 1862, June 26) – {{ill|Minasaku Motohachi|ja|箕作元八|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minasaku Motohachi|qq=}}, a historian and the fourth son of Minasaku Akutsubo (died [[:en:1919|1919]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Kenkyū|Kenkyū]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1193|1193]] [[:en:June 29|June 29]]) – {{ill|Soga Jigorō Tokuchi|ja|曾我五郎時致|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Soga Jigorō Tokuchi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 曾我時致}}, a samurai and the younger brother of Soga (born [[:en:1174|1174]]). * [[Tenmei]] 8th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1788|1788]] [[:en:July 2|July 2]]) – {{ill|Goryōken Kayū|ja|呉陵軒可有|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Goryōken Kayū|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, a miscellaneous haiku writer known as "Yanudaru" (柳多留). * [[:en:Bunka|Bunka]] 14th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1817|1817]] [[:en:July 13|July 13]]) – {{ill|Kaiho Seiryō|ja|海保青陵|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaiho Seiryō|qq=}}, a Confucian scholar and economic reformer (born [[:en:1755|1755]]).
